In Python, the equivalent of Julia's struct for simplifying data construction is typically handled by using classes, specifically using the dataclass from the dataclasses module

In Julia, the typeof function is used to determine the type of a variable or an expression. In Python, you can achieve a similar result using the type() function, which returns the type of the object passed to it.

